qscintilla2
-------------------------------------------
QScintilla is a port to Qt of Neil Hodgson's Scintilla C++ editor class.

As well as features found in standard text editing components, 
QScintilla includes features especially useful when editing and 
debugging source code. These include support for syntax styling, error 
indicators, code completion and call tips. The selection margin can 
contain markers like those used in debuggers to indicate breakpoints and 
the current line. Styling choices are more open than with many editors, 
allowing the use of proportional fonts, bold and italics, multiple 
foreground and background colours and multiple fonts. 

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.5-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3
  libQtCore4-4.6.2-1
  libQtGui4-4.6.2-1
  libstdc++6-4.3.4-3
(python-qscintilla2)
  python-2.5.5-10
  python-pyqt4-4.7.3-1
  python-sip-4.10.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding devel packages)
  binutils-2.20.51-1
  cygport-0.9.83-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  gcc4-g++-4.3.4-3
  make-3.81-2

Canonical homepage:
  http://www.riverbankcomputing.com/software/qscintilla/

Canonical download:
  http://www.riverbankcomputing.com/static/download/QScintilla2/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack qscintilla2-2.4.3-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./qscintilla2-2.4.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libqscintilla2_5-2.4.3-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libqscintilla2-common-2.4.3-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libqscintilla2-devel-2.4.3-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/python-pyqt4-qsci-2.4.3-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/qscintilla2-2.4.3-X-src.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

